 The\ndirectionality of transmission of guided light through the array of atoms is a\nconsequence of the existence of a longitudinal component of the guided light\nfield as well as the ellipticity of both the field polarization and the atomic\ndipole vector.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Feb 2015 23:46:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 17 May 2015 13:35:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
